        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 10:13PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 1012 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated a cluster of thunderstorms
along a line extending from near Melvin to near Emmett to
Marysville. Movement was southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts near 40 mph and heavy rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could damage unsecured objects. Localized
flooding is possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Yale around 1015 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Avoca, Fargo, Lynn
Township, Goodells, Brockway, Ruby, Smiths Creek, and Wadhams.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
